Question: Meaning how did he purpose? Was it really special when it happened?
Answer: Oh okay. My apologies there. Well. We were up on the levee back home where I was born and raised and again we were up on the Mississippi Levee. the Mississippi Levee where we were at is located in Louisiana but it's the Mississippi River and we were standing on the Levee. Absolutely beautiful. This is a destination that my grandfather used to go to nearly every single day in the morning and even sometimes in the evening to enjoy its beauty and just to take in the nature, to watch the boats come by and to look at the bridge... the giant skyscrapers  and planes helicopters and more. There were also be periodically different events that happened up here.  But most the time was peaceful and quiet. Awesome place to visit. Unfortunately my grandfather passed away a few years back  plus my grandmother soon after sadly... They mean a lot to me. They partly raised me with my mom. They played a big role in my life. I love my grandparents. but this is a memory that I will always remember about him, my Paw paw and I love going to this place while we were there one day he got down on one knee after making a joke that he saw a trash boat in the water got my attention because I wanted to see it turned back around and he was on one knee asking me to marry him. Which the joke that he made was something similar to what my grandfather would say it was very touching, very sweet and very just emotional altogether. I loved it I couldn't have asked for a better proposal. but altogether I find that very special and I just loved it loved it. That's how my husband proposed to me.
